  "prompt": "In no more than 200 words please describe a time you gave remarkable service to one of your customer?",
  "response": "I once provided remarkable service to a customer during my tenure at a tech support center. The customer, an elderly woman, was struggling to connect with her family overseas via video call due to her outdated laptop and limited technical knowledge. Sensing her frustration and loneliness, I went beyond the standard protocol. \n\nAfter resolving her immediate connectivity issue, I spent additional time to patiently guide her through the basics of using video conferencing software. Recognizing her need for a more sustainable solution, I coordinated with our hardware team to expedite the delivery of a new, user-friendly laptop tailored to her needs, which we set up for her remotely.\n\nI also arranged a follow-up session to ensure she was comfortable with the new system. A week later, she called back, not with a problem, but to express her gratitude. She shared how she was now regularly connecting with her family, which significantly improved her emotional well-being. This experience underscored the impact of personalized service and empathy in customer interactions.",
